JAVASCRIPT
    is a programming language initially designed to interact with elements of webpages

    3 main parts:
        core functionality - ECMASCRIPT(europe company  manfactured association)
        -ES5/ES6/ESNIEXT
        document object model(DOM)-
            :provides interfacs for interactingwith elements on web pages.
        Browser Object model(BOM)-
            provides the browser API interacting with web browser.
    
    JIT-Just-in-Time compiler
        Brended Eich-1995-netscape developer
        Mocha
        Live Script
        Java Script
        
        JAVASCRIPT has a feature
        1)daynamic:meaning the variables can be reassigned values in any type
        2)object orented programming:it supports eith the object protocoltype and classes
        3)functional:functions can be created via expressions and passed like otherobjects
        4)syntax:it is based on java and c language
        5)cross-platform:JS is a cross-platform language
        ^)Free:it is alread runing in most browser

        JAVASCRIPT was standarized in 1997 by european computer manfacture association(ECMA)
        as ECMA  .the first addition fa this standrad was published in june 1997

        ECMAScript 5,also know as ES5was standardized in december 2009 as part of the ECMA-262 specification.itintoduce several important feature and improvment to JS lang,includeing strict mode,support for JSON,newn array method

