 IBM   EX:
 ******

var weight=55;
var height=1.82;
var bmi=weight/(height*height);
var category="";
switch(true){
    case bmi <18.5:
        category="underweight";
        break;
        case bmi>=18.5&&bmi <24.9:
            category = "normal weight";
            break;
            case bmi= "overweight":
            break;
            case bmi >= 30:
            category = "invalid Bmi";
}
console.log("bmi :", bmi.toFixed(2),categtory)

while loop
************

while loop loops through a block of code as long as the specified condition evaluate true
as soon as the condition fails, the loop is stoped

var i=0;
while(1<10){
    console.log(i);
    i++;
}

do-while loop
***************
with a do while loop the block code executed once and then condition is evaluated if the condition is 
true the statement is  repeat as long as specified condition evaluated to is true
the generic syntsx of the do-while loop is:

do{
    //code to beexecuted
}